  "Stars build heavier elements by fusing lighter ones: H → He → C → O → ... → Fe. Each stage requires higher temperatures and pressures.": "",
  "Iron (Fe) is significant in stellar fusion because:": "",
  "Iron cannot exist in stars": "",
  "Iron fusion produces the most energy": "",
  "Iron is the lightest element": "",
  "Fusing elements heavier than iron consumes energy rather than releasing it": "",
  "Iron-56 has the highest binding energy per nucleon. Fusing elements beyond iron is endothermic (energy-consuming), which is why stars cannot sustain fusion past iron and may collapse into supernovae.": "",
