  "Why does fusion require extremely high temperatures (millions of degrees)?": "",
  "To melt the nuclei into liquid": "",
  "To remove all electrons first": "",
  "To overcome the electrostatic repulsion between positively charged nuclei": "",
  "To slow the nuclei down enough to combine": "",
  "Nuclei are positively charged and repel each other. Only at extreme temperatures do they move fast enough to overcome this Coulomb barrier and get close enough for the strong nuclear force to bind them.": "",
